(1, 'Education', 'Feed Your Knowledge', 'Best Education', 'Education For EveryOne ', 'We are proud to be the Best', 'For Your Better Future ', 'To develop a country and the world the future should be secure and the children are the weapons to build the nation with all their knowledge and education.', 'To discover and develop the natural talent or gift in Nigerian child, lay a solid Foundation and achieve Moral and academic excellence towards realizing Parental and National Educational goals.', 'Discipline<br>\r\nHonesty <br>\r\nHoliness<br>\r\nDiligence <br>\r\nIntegrity', 'Our curriculum is unique as it ensures that our children are global Citizens and also become proud of their Nigerian heritage. It is based on Nigerian and British curricula.', 'The students have access to ICT room stocked with over two hundred computers. This gives the students access to e- library, e- notes, CBT, and fully automated e-learning process with full multimedia for computer Assisted Learning.', '<p>BRIEF HISTORY</p>\r\n\r\n<p>D &ndash; Way international Primary School was officially founded in September, 2001. It was not quite long [3 years later] that the college was founded and approved while the annex was established in year 2008.&nbsp; It has been approved for both WAEC, NECO as well as GCE WAEC. The first WAEC was written in year 2005.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>MEET OUR:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PROPRIETOR </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Picture</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Engr. S.A Olagbaju</p>\r\n\r\n<p>08023392713</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>PROPRIETRESS</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Picture</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mrs. E.A Olagbaju</p>\r\n\r\n<p>08055947585</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>BOARD OF DIRECTORS</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr. Kolawole Olagbaju</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr. James Olagbaju</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dr. Mrs. Sholademi</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mrs Ogunleye Ronke</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dr. Mrs Ijaleye Tosin</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr. Seyi Olayiwola</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>GOVERNING BOARD</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pro. J. O Oyundoyin- Faculty of Education, UI</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pro. P.A Amosun &ndash; Department of Teacher Education, UI</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dr. Olasunkanmi Isreal &ndash; Department of Science and Technology Education, UI</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>PRINCIPALS </em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Main</strong> School : Mrs A.B Ojo</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Annex</strong> : Mrs Kehinde Adetokunbo</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ADMISSION</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Application forms are obtainable online and in the school premises. Qualified candidates are admitted into JSS1-2 and SS1-2.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Requirements for candidates:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Two passport photograph</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Copy of Birth certificate</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Primary school testimonial and placement slip</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Recent statement of result</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Examination Date</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Entrance examination holds every third Saturday of the month of April, May, June, July, August, and September. Applicant into JSS1 must attain minimum of age 10.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>OPENING HOURS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Monday to Friday &ndash; 7.30am to 5.00pm</strong></p>\r\n', '<p>ADMISSION INTO JSS 1 FOR 2021/2022 ACADEMIC SESSION</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Applications are invited from suitably qualified candidates for admission into&nbsp;JSS 1 for 2021/2022 Academic Session.&nbsp;Application forms are obtainable online. The admission form is ten thousand naira&nbsp;(N10,000.00) only.&nbsp;This amount also includes the cost of downloading past questions from the website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>REQUIREMENTS FOR CANDIDATES:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Those who will be eligible for admission into JSS 1 for 2021/2022 academic session&nbsp;MUST be ten (10) years old by September, 2021.&nbsp;Candidates will be required to present originals and photocopies of their birth certificates during interview.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HOW TO APPLY FOR THE DLHS ADMISSION FORM</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Fill the admission Payment Form and click on&nbsp;&quot;SUBMIT&quot;</li>\r\n	<li>After submitting the Payment form, you will be presented with the payment options available. The first is the online payment option, pay with your Naira Master card, Verve card or GT Pay and the second is payment at any GT Bank Branch in Nigeria, Print the payment slip and pay at any GT Bank .</li>\r\n	<li>After Payment, Note down your PINCODE (Without The PINCODE You will not be able to fill the admission form).</li>\r\n	<li>Visit this website to fill the admission form.</li>\r\n	<li>Go to Admission Menu and Click on Application form, verify your&nbsp;PINCODE&nbsp;to fill and printout the online form.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>The Examination slip will be printed along with the form. The Examination slip is needed for accreditation at the Exam center. Use your pincode to download the past questions from the website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>REQUIRED TEXT BOOKS FOR SS1- SS3</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:30px\">\r\n			<p><strong>1.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:271px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Civic education Text</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:323px\">\r\n			<p>New Standard Civic Education For Senior Secondary Schools (<strong>By Alexander O.A)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:30px\">\r\n			<p><strong>2.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:271px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Government Text</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:323px\">\r\n			<p>Essential Government for SS1- SS3</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>OR</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Comprehensive Government for SS1 &ndash; SS3</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:30px\">\r\n			<p><strong>3.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:271px\">\r\n			<p><strong>English Text</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:323px\">\r\n			<p>New Concept and New Oxford Secondary English Course for Seni