s number. Rather, if there is any communication to be made, it goes through the administrative office.</li>\r\n	<li><u>Open day:</u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The school observes a day in a term when parents of the school come to see their children&rsquo;s performance and interact with the teachers of their child / ward. Parents should be careful not to exchange phone numbers or gifts. Everything should be done through the Office.</li>\r\n	<li><u>Writing Materials/ Snacks:</u> The pupils of the school are not allowed to come to school with any writing material, snacks or object of any kind apart from their lunch &amp; water. The Nursery school pupils are allowed to come to school with their snacks or fruits not sweets or chewing gum.</li>\r\n	<li><u>Uniform pattern:</u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The school has a unique uniform for her pupils: the Polo of the day goes with Blue Jean, Jacket, White trainers &amp; White Stockings.</li>\r\n	<li>Red Polo {wt collar} &amp; red cap</li>\r\n	<li>: Green Polo, White &amp; Green cap</li>\r\n	<li>: White Polo &amp; Blue cap</li>\r\n	<li>: Same as Monday</li>\r\n	<li>: Same as Wednesday</li>\r\n	<li>Decent wears with shoe/sandals <u>NOT </u>Slippers, Bum shorts, sleeveless, tights, leggings or transparent wears.</li>\r\n	<li><u>Transportation system:</u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The children are expected to wait for the school bus in their various bus posts and not the drivers waiting. No parent is expected to give drivers message for the school management or call him/ her for an official message. It must be done through the administrative office.</li>\r\n	<li><u>Lesson:</u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Parents are not expected to contact any teacher for any form of private home lesson for their kids, as this is against the ethics of the school.</li>\r\n	<li>The school does not observe Public holidays except Children&rsquo;s Day and Independence Day, therefore any day your child will be absent from school, communicate through the Administrative office.</li>\r\n	<li>Any child of the school is free to celebrate his/ her birthday in the school. This comes up from Monday to Thursday. The gift items must get to the School before 12pm. Chocolates, Sweets, Chewing gum or cooked food are not allowed. Remember to communicate to the school earlier on the date.</li>\r\n	<li>The homework given to the kids is for them to handle it themselves. Parents/ Guardians are not permitted to write their children&rsquo;s homework.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>NB: Visiting Day is every last Saturday of the month. Time: 9am &ndash; 5pm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No student comes in with any cloth except the ones recommended by the school</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Parents are expected to come with just a plate of food and a bottle of soft drink.</li>\r\n	<li>No pencil Skirts or Trousers will be allowed and must be below the knee.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt\">We, &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; Have read and agreed to abide by the rules &amp; regulations guiding the school</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt\">Sign: &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt\">Date: &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.&nbsp; Phone: &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ROYAL AMBASSADOORS FOUNDATION SECONDARY SCHOOL, </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ONITSHA</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>HOSTEL REQUIREMENTS</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:57px\">\r\n			<p>S/N</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"